cs.NE, cs.AR, cs.ET, cs.LG, cs.EM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper presents a design of a reservoir network approach, which is a type of neural network. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on the implementation of the design in FPGA hardware. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is a possible category as the paper introduces a novel re-seeding method to reduce the adverse effects of stochastic noise, which may be considered an emerging technology. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the design on classification and regression problems. 
- cs.EM (Engineering Mathematics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper uses metrics such as kernel quality and generalization rank to analyze the design.
